Source: dhtnet
Section: net
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Louis Maillard <louis.maillard@savoirfairelinux.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 12), cmake, pkg-config
Standards-Version: 4.7.0
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://git.jami.net/savoirfairelinux/dhtnet
Vcs-Git: https://git.jami.net/savoirfairelinux/dhtnet.git

Package: libdhtnet0
Section: libs
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: peer-to-peer networking runtime library
 dhtnet provides a lightweight C++ library to establish secure peer-to-peer
 connections identified by public keys (no central server). It offers helpers
 for NAT traversal (ICE, TURN, UPNP), secure channels (TLS/DTLS), multiplexed
 sockets, and credential management.

Package: libdhtnet-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Depends: libdhtnet0 (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: development files for libdhtnet (headers, pkg-config)
 This package contains the headers, pkg-config file, and other development
 resources required to build applications against libdhtnet.

Package: dhtnet
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, libdhtnet0 (= ${binary:Version})
Recommends: dhtnet-crtmgr
Description: peer-to-peer networking tools and daemon
 This package provides the command line utilities and server components built
 on top of libdhtnet: dnc (daemon), dhtnet-crtmgr (certificate manager), dsh
 (shell), dvpn (VPN helper) and related helper tools.

